article.headline: St. Joseph's beats Valparaiso 31-10
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Tate Borlik threw two touchdowns to Mike Anderson and Anderson ran for another TD as St. Joseph's beat Valparaiso 31-10 on Saturday. Borlik finished 16 of 30 and 170 yards passing. Anderson's 47-yard touchdown run came with just seconds remaining in the first quarter. He had 97 yards rushing on 10 carries. Braxton Shelton -- who scored on a 4-yard touchdown run in the fourth quarter to seal the win -- led St. Joseph's in rushing with 159 yards on 25 carries. Gavin Voss kicked a 46-yard field goal to end the first half. The Pumas (1-0) had 464 yards in total offense. The Pumas led 17-3 at the break and expanded their advantage to 24-3 early in the third quarter before the Crusaders (0-2) finally scored a touchdown on an 11-yard pass from Ben Lehman to Andrew Cassara. Lehman was 24 of 47 for 234 yards.
